    • Method Detail

      • leveledUp

        boolean leveledUp()
        Checks if the level-up widget is visible
        Returns:
        Returns true if the widget is visible

      • xpGained

        boolean xpGained()
        Checks if the XP gained has changed since the last check. The default resetThreshold is 4000ms(4s). Meaning the checks will reset itself and invalidate the last call after 4s of not calling the method.
        Returns:
        true if XP has changed, false otherwise

      • xpGained

        boolean xpGained​(int resetThreshold)
        Checks if the XP gained has changed since the last check.
        Parameters:
        resetThreshold - the maximum allowed duration before resetting the check, call this if you want to specify your own reset time, e.g. if the default is too short/too long.
        Returns:
        true if XP has changed, false otherwise

      • isIdle

        boolean isIdle()
        Checks if the player is idle based on the median pixel shift. This method determines whether the player is currently idle by calculating the median pixel shift over a set of recent frames. It compares the median shift to a predefined threshold to determine if there is significant movement. If the shift is below the threshold, the player is considered idle.
        Returns:
        true if the player is idle (i.e., the median pixel shift is below the threshold), false otherwise.

      • currentPixelShift

        double currentPixelShift()
        Calculates the current median pixel shift for the player. This method computes the pixel shift between the current frame and the last frame captured, and stores the shift in a rolling cache. It then calculates the median of the pixel shifts stored in the cache to smooth out short-term fluctuations. The median shift can be used to analyze whether the player is moving or idle.
        Returns:
        the current median pixel shift as a double. If the cache is reset due to frame expiration, the shift will be 0.0 until new data is gathered.

      • within

        boolean within​(Area areaToSearchIn)
        Gets the player's current position and checks if it is within the specified area
        Parameters:
        areaToSearchIn - This is the Area of the custom map you want to check if you are in.
        Returns:
        Returns a true/false boolean, true if you are in the RegionBox, false if not.

      • atTile

        boolean atTile​(Tile tileToCheck)
        Checks if player is at that specific tile within your set worldmap
        Parameters:
        tileToCheck - The tile to be checked for presence within the region defined in the map file.
        Returns:
        true if the player is on the tile in the specified map, false otherwise.

      • isTileWithinArea

        boolean isTileWithinArea​(Tile tileToCheck,
                         Area areaToCheckWithin)
        Checks if a given tile is within a specified area.

        This method determines whether the provided tile (represented by tileToCheck) is located within the bounds of the area defined by areaToCheckWithin.

        Parameters:
        tileToCheck - The tile whose presence within the area is being checked.
        areaToCheckWithin - The area within which the tile's presence is checked.
        Returns:
        true if tileToCheck is within the bounds of areaToCheckWithin, false otherwise.

      • tileEquals

        boolean tileEquals​(Tile originTile,
                   Tile tileToCheck)
        Compares two tiles for equality.

        This method checks if the specified originTile and tileToCheck represent the same tile.

        Parameters:
        originTile - The first tile to be compared.
        tileToCheck - The second tile to be compared with the first tile.
        Returns:
        true if both tiles are considered equal, false otherwise.

      • waitTillMoving

        boolean waitTillMoving​(int checkTimes)
        Checks if we are moving within a predefined number of position checks. The method continuously compares the current position of the device against its last recorded position. Movement is detected if the position changes at least once during the specified checks.
        Parameters:
        checkTimes - the number of times the device's position is checked for movement
        Returns:
        true if movement is detected within the given checks; false otherwise

      • waitTillNotMoving

        boolean waitTillNotMoving​(int checkTimes)
        Verifies that the specified device remains stationary over a series of position checks. The method checks the device's position repeatedly to ensure that it does not change. If the position remains unchanged for the consecutive checks specified, the method concludes that the device is not moving.
        Parameters:
        checkTimes - the number of times the device's position is checked for lack of movement
        Returns:
        true if no movement is detected across all checks; false if any movement is detected
